<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278756>
    dc:description "PLATE 108. A. Gonatopus pedestris, female from Italy, lateral view. Length 3.0 mm. B. Mesosoma, lateral view of G. rufoniger (=G. indianus Olmi), from India. Length 2.0 mm. C. Female of G. bicolor, lateral view. Lenght 2.9 mm. D. G. acuminatus, holotype, lateral view. Length 3.12 mm. (From Olmi 1984)" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278756/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278800>
    dc:description "PLATE 122. A. Male, lateral view. B–D. Male genitalia. E. Chela, holotype. A. Gonatopus flavifemur (=Dicondylus indianus Olmi) from India. Length 2.6 mm. B. G. flavifemur from Australia. C. G. lucens from Japan. D. G. pedestris from Finland. E. G. lucens. Scale bar 0.17 mm for B, 0.10 mm for C, 0.15 mm for D and 0.19 mm for E. (From Olmi 1984)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278800/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278804>
    dc:description "PLATE 123. Gonatopus pedestris. A. Female from Turkey, Kuracasile, dorsal view. Length 3.0 mm (from Olmi 1999a). B. Chela of female from Italy, Vercelli (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.14 mm for B." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278804/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278808>
    dc:description "PLATE 124. Gonatopus pedestris, male from Italy. Length 2.8 mm. A. Dorsal view (from Olmi 1984). B. Lateral view (from Olmi 1999a)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278808/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278832>
    dc:description "PLATE 130. A, E. Heads, frontal view. B. Head, dorsal view. C, H. Mesosoma, lateral view. D, F, I. Chelae. G. Mesosoma, dorsal view. A–D. Gonatopus philippinus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). E, F. G. plebeius, female from Indonesia (from Olmi 1984). G–I. G.rufoniger (=G. indianus), holotype (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 1.60 mm for A and B, 0.91 mm for C, 0.19 mm for D, 1.22 mm for E, 0.18 mm for F, 0.61 mm for G and H, 0.25 mm for I." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278832/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278818>
    dc:description "PLATE 127. A. Mesosoma. B. Scutum and metathorax + propodeum. C, D, F–H. Chelae. E. Head. A, C. Gonatopus daunus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). B, D. G. fyanensis (=G. magnus), holotype (from Olmi 1984). E, F. G. hainanensis, holotype (E from Olmi 2003; F from Olmi 1986). G. G. iarensis (=G. bouceki), holotype (from Olmi 1987c). H. G. javanus (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.20 mm for C, 0.29 mm for D, 0.31 mm for F, 0.26 mm for G and 0.22 mm for H." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278818/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278824>
    dc:description "PLATE 128. A, B. Male genitalia. C. Head, holotype. D, F, G. Chelae, holotypes. E. Scutum and metathorax + propodeum, holotype. A. Gonatopus javanus from Japan. B. G. maurus from China (from Xu et al. 2006c). C, D. G. lankanus (from Olmi 2003). E, F. G.lucidus (from Olmi 1984). G. G. maurus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.18 mm for A and G, 0.13 mm for B, 0.31 mm for D, 0.56 mm for E, 0.24 mm for F." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278824/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278812>
    dc:description "PLATE 125. A–D, F. Chelae, holotypes. E. Mesosoma, holotype. A. Gonatopus achterbergi (from Olmi 1991). B. G. attenuatus (from Olmi 1984). C. G. beaveri (from Olmi 1998e). D. G. besucheti (from Olmi 1991). E, F. G. cantonensis (from Olmi 1987c). Scale bar 0.23 mm for A, 0.30 mm for B and F, 0.35 mm for C, 0.17 mm for D, 0.95 mm for E." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278812/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278850>
    dc:description "PLATE 136. Esagonatopus sinensis sp. nov., holotype. A. Chela. B. Mesosoma, lateral view. C. Mesosoma, dorsal view. Scale bar 0.10 mm for A, 0.40 mm for B and C." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278850/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278816>
    dc:description "PLATE 126. A. Dorsal view. Length 7.5 mm. B, D, E. Heads. C. Mesosoma. F. Chela. A–C, F. Gonatopus cristatus (=Megagonatopus birmanus Olmi & Currado, 1976), female from Myanmar (from Olmi & Currado, 1976). D, E. Gonatopus daunus, holotype, frontal view (D) and dorsal view (E) (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 2.27 mm for B, 1.55 mm for C, 0.94 mm for D and E, 0.36 mm for F." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278816/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278828>
    dc:description "PLATE 129. A–C, E. Chelae. D. Vertex of head. A. Gonatopus medius, holotype (from Olmi 1984). B. G.mysorensis, holotype (from Olmi 1984). C. G. nivosus (=G. delhiensis Olmi) from India (from Olmi 1987c). D, E. G. perpolitus, female from Indonesia (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.35 mm for A, 0.25 mm for B, 0.22 mm for C, 0.61 mm for D and 0.17 mm for E." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278828/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278752>
    dc:description "PLATE 107. Chelae, holotypes. A. Gonatopus paulyi (from Olmi 1986). B. G.abjectus (from Olmi 1984). C. G. bengalensis (from Olmi 1984). D. G. lucens (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.15 mm for A, 0.14 mm for B, 0.21 mm for C and 0.20 mm for D." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278752/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278836>
    dc:description "PLATE 131. A–D. Male genitalia. E,G, I. Mesosoma. F, H, J.Chelae, holotypes. A. Gonatopus rufoniger from China. B, I, J. G. superbus (from Olmi 1987c). C. G. asiaticus from Japan. D. G. leurosipropodeus, holotype (from He & Xu, 2002). E, F. G. schenklingi, holotype (from Olmi 1984). G, H. G. sitae (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.19 mm for A, 0.18 mm for B, 0.15 mm for C, 0.17 mm for D, 0.21 mm for F, 0.34 mm for H, and 0.32 mm for J." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278836/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278840>
    dc:description "PLATE 132. Chelae, holotypes. A. Gonatopus thai (from Olmi 1984). B. G. viet (from Olmi 1986). C. G. viraktamathi (from Olmi 1987c). D. G.yasumatsui(from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.26 mm for A, 0.15 mm for B, 0.37 mm for C and 0.22 mm for D." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278840/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

